post.description:
Post one or several dicom(s) to Milvue API, in Multipart/Related format (STOW).

Dicoms should be part of the same study.

Example:
```
curl --header "x-goog-meta-owner: <my-api-key>" --header "Content-Type: multipart/related; type=application/dicom" --form "file1=@<dicom1>;type=application/dicom" --form "file2=@<dicom2.dcm>;type=application/dicom" -X POST "https://dev.predict.milvue.com/v3/studies"
```

schema.title: Response Post Multipart V3 V3 Studies Post

get.description:
GET the status for a given study.

Example:
```
curl --header "x-goog-meta-owner: <my-api-key>" --header "Accept: application/json" -X GET "https://dev.predict.milvue.com/v3/studies/<my-StudyInstanceUID>/status"
```
Return:
- A json with the prediction status (e.g. `running`)

GET a study from Milvue API, in Multipart/Related format (WADO).

Example:
```
curl --header "x-goog-meta-owner: <my-api-key>" --header "Accept: multipart/related; type=application/dicom; transfer-syntax=*, application/json" -X GET "https://dev.predict.milvue.com/v3/studies/<my-StudyInstanceUID>?inference_command=smarturgences" --output "response_content.txt"
```
Return:
- 1. A multipart/related response with several `application/dicom` parts.

OR

- 2. A json with the prediction status (e.g. `running`): a raw json if the header `Accept: ...` contains `application/json`, or encapsulated in a multipart message otherwise.

__Note: the prefered way to get a prediction status is to use `/v3/studies/<my-StudyInstanceUID>/status`. This route should be mainly used to get dicoms, via dicomweb protocol (option 1 above).__

post.description:
Flag a study as interesting.

Example:
```
curl -H "x-goog-meta-owner: <my-api-key>" -X POST https://dev.predict.milvue.com/v3/interesting/<my-StudyInstanceUID>
```

Usage: report errors or raise attention on specific cases.

Note:
- __the study must have been sent to Milvue API before being posted here__
- it's easier for Milvue to retrieve a specific case if it was flagged as interesting

APIKeyHeader.description:
Authentication is done via an API key in the request's header:
```
"x-goog-meta-owner: <my-api-key>"
```
where `<my-api-key>` is a uuid-v4 (e.g. `22209633-26ea-4b35-a197-e55c375dc36f`).

The API key is unique for each user (clinics) and provided by Milvue.
APIKeyHeader.name: x-goog-meta-owner
